inn1.comm: 120kmh, on length and well outside off, left alone with a forward lean
125kmh, back of length and shaping away this time, left again
back of length outside off again, he leaves it off the back foot
pitched up little bit outside off again, he lets it go

makes him play and makes him miss, bowled him! This beautiful delivery had its seam shaping away as it pitched outside off, but landed on the seam and came in as Hafeez presented his bat but the ball sneaked through the gate
heading towards off stump again, Younis goes back and blocks it
outside the off stump on good length, shaping in a bit, left alone
wider outside the off stump, left again easily
good-length delivery outside off with the angle, lets it go
angles it across again from well outside off, left easily
down the leg side this time with inswing and it's a wide
pitched up outside off and he drives it down to mid off
swings it in again, goes down leg again, wide again
back to the line and length outside off, Shehzad back to leaving again
draws him forward and gets a thickish outside edge with a length delivery and outswing, that went wide of second slip to third man
on length outside the off stump, he leans forward and blocks it
shapes it away a little bit from well outside off, left eaisly
125kmh, fuller outside off with some shape, pushed down towards mid off
good bounce as this was more or less on length outside off, was left again and carried well to Ronchi

Shehzad was only halfway down the pitch when the ball crossed the stumps at bowler's end! He pushed the full ball back down the ground, it deflected off Mills' leg and went to mid on and they set off for the run. Anderson put in a slide and threw it quickly, catching Shehzad light years out of his crease
bit too full outside off, beautifully driven through the covers but cover gets a hand to it
back of length outside off with the angle, left alone
he leans forward and lets this one go too, outside off
touch closer to off from back of length, Younis blocks it towards point
swings it away from good length outside off, Younis lets it go
back of length outside off again, he stays back and defends solidly
128kph, nice shape from Kills just outside off on length, draws a thick outside off to point
bit too full and that's driven to mid off
full on the leg side, deflected off the pads behind square on leg for a leg bye
back of length outside the off stump, he defends it off the back foot
on good length outside off this time, pushed with a forward lean on off
around length on the fourth-stump line outside off, defended again
140kmh, angled across outside the off stump, left alone
on length outside off, he leans forward a bit and lets that go too
too full outside off and he drives it down on a knee just over Guptill at backward point, Anderson runs from third man and slides to keep it to two
outside the off stump on length, left again
fullish again, driven nicely into the coves where Nathan dives to his right and stops it
back of length outside off, he defends with soft hands for one but there's no time. About three fielders run in from somewhere
shaping it in nicely towards off stump, Younis pushes it down to mid in
fullish outside off and Younis pounces on that by caressing it along the ground with a cover drive for four. First four of the morning

oh Younis has given his wicket away! He slashes at the back of length delivery outside off and hit it too hard as a thick top edge flew right to third man. They are checking for the new ball, oh, Mill's foot lands on the line, that's a no ball. What a reprieve for Younis and Pakistan

full toss is slapped down half-heartedly towards mid on and Shehzad was being absolutely casual about the quick single there, not dragging his bat properly. Would have been in danger if that was a direct hit at the bowler's end
short of length outside off and he defends it back
shapes it in towards the batsman, Younis defends and looks for a run but is sent back
tries to cut the short of length ball outside off, gets a bottom edge towards point
another inside edge as he looked to push this one outside off, hit his back foot with the edge
140kmh, on length now outside off, blocked back to the bowler
gets some width and he drives that beautifully with excellent timing to place it between point and cover point for four
finds the gap again as he charges down this time and punches the back of length ball to beat Nathan at cover point for four more

nearly three in a row! This was driven nicely through the covers as it was pitched up a bit and the fielder ran hard to slide it in. Only two because Shehzad thought that would go for four, poor running again
and beats him! Slightly short of length outside off, Shehzad drives and misses
136kmh, starts with a wide down the leg side
chases and misses, but called wide outside off now. It shaped away from well outside off as Younis drove and missed
too full outside off and he pushes it down to mid off for a quick single
angling in a bit towards off stump, punched down to mid on
that's too close to off to cut, he tries without any footwork and misses
slashes but misses again! This was wider outside off and shaped away further, Shehzad swung and missed
147kmh, beaten by the extra bounce this time! Back of length outside off, nice bounce as Shehzad threw his bat but only to miss
146kmh, ends the over very well by beating him again! Touch back of length outside off, he didn't move his feet much for the drive and missed it
back of length angling in form well outside off, punched to cover
punches it again and manages an inside edge close to the stumps behind square on leg for one

he's gone, caught behind! Shehzad came down the track, Boult responded with a full and wide delivery outside off, he threw his bat with a full stretch, taking it on the full, and got an edge for the keeper
bangs it in outside off and angles it in, Misbah blocks it back
leans forward and runs that down to third man from outside off with soft hands
back of length and outside off, pushed down towards mid off
143kmh, fullish outside off, pushed down towards mid on
144kmh, swings it in little bit, Misbah's defence doesn't go too far from the stumps on the leg side, they sneak a run
139kph, bangs in a short one outside off with outswing, he lets it go
slightly full outside the off stump, driven down straight to mid off
swings it in dangerously towards off from full length, Younis drives it to cover
too full outside off, driven nicely in the gap and that's excellent teamwork as Baz dives and passes the ball to his brother who throws the ball back in no time
fullish delivery outside off, pushes down to mid off

loud appeal for lbw, given! This one swung in sharply from length to beat Younis' bat as he looked to whip it away. Younis reviews that, but he's struck in front of middle and that's hitting leg stump. Younis goes back
welcomes him with a bouncer and he sways out of the line
length delivery angling away from outside off, left alone
that's too wide outside off and Sohail doesn't move his feet much but drives it away for four
beaten! This one swung away from off stump as Sohail looked to defend it but doesn't connect
presses forward to push the delivery to cover point
leans forward again and pushes this one into the covers
blocks this one off the front foot outside off
144kmh, there comes the bouncer outside off and Misbah ducks under it
guides that behind square with a forward lean and backward point dives to his left to stop that with one hand
bit too full and Misbah drives that nicely through the covers for four. High elbow + nice timing + down on a knee = four runs
touch short of length around off, defends on the off side
some outswing from outside off and it's helped to third man for one
leans forward and pushes the length ball to backward point
back of length well outside off he, lets it go
wider outside off with some late swing, left again
moves towards off stump and defends it off the front foot
144kmh, back of length towards the off stump, defends it off the back foot
bit of room from short of length and he guides it to third man for one
back of length and angling in, tucked to square leg. The fielder gets a direct hit and concedes an overthrow
back of length outside the off stump, left alone by Misbah
143kmh, short ball this time outside off, Misbah sways out of the line
another short of length delivery, he defends it on the off side and that's drinks
angles it away from outside off, left alone
short ball this time and he pulls it away for two wide of mid on
full on the stumps and that's driven down to hit the stumps
on length on the off stump, pushes to point off the front foot
length delivery is too wide outside the off stump, called wide
towards the off stump and he blocks it back
falls short of slip! This was angling away from outside off, he poked and a thick outside off didn't carry to first slip and went for four
fullish around off, driven to cover
on middle and leg now, helped to midwicket
he goes back this time and tucks it off the pads towards square leg for one
length delivery on off is blocked back
leans forward and pushes the ball back to the bowler
pushed down the ground on leg and it goes past the bowler to long on
back of length on the leg stump, helped to midwicket
length delivery on the off stump, defends on the off side this time
bit too full on off and it's driven down straight to mid off
back of length on middle and leg, tucked to leg for a quick single
angled in towards the off stump, pushed back
back of length outside off, cut to point off the back foot
middle and length delivery, tucked to square leg for one
goes on the back foot to whip it to leg but takes it on the thigh pad
that's gone all the way! Saw the fuller delivery and Misbah lofted it with the turn on the leg side over the midwicket boundary for six
flatter outside off, pushed down off the back foot
helped with the turn to the square leg region for one
length delivery on off, turned to the leg side and an overthrow leads to the second run
back of length outside off, stays on the back foot to defend
short of length again, defends it close to himself and takes a quick single
on middle on length, pushed down to mid off this time
gets width and steers it away in the gap between point and cover point for four. Excellent timing and gets four
fuller outside off, driven to cover off the front foot
touch back of length on middle and off, defended on the back foot
on length on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler
pitched up little and Misbah unleashes another six, this time with a slog sweep over the square leg boundary with the turn
presses forward and blocks it on the off side
loud appeal for lbw as Misbah tries the reverse sweep, and it's turned down! Nathan and Ronchi have a word and decide not to review, good choice as it pitched outside leg
fuller on the pads, helped to deep backward square leg for one
comes down the track and pushes it down to long on for one
full outside off, driven to mid off
back of length outside the off stump, pushed to cover point
on the pads this time, tucked to mid on
length delivery on middle and leg, helped towards midwicket for one
back of length outside off, pushed to point off the back foot
moves to off stump and defends it to the leg side for a quick single
outside off and turning in, cut off the back foot to deep point for one
nearly in the block hole, he digs it out to the leg side
takes a step down and pushes it to the leg side
full on the stumps again, pushed towards midwicket
outside off on length, defended into the coves
leans forward and blocks it back
angled in from outside off, tucked to the leg side behind square for one
strikes on his second ball! Wasn't a great delivery - it was short and wide, Sohail cut it off the back foot and Guptill dived to his left to grab it with both hands
back of length outside off, defends off the back foot
stays in the crease and defends it on off again
pushes it off the back foot to cover point
pretty wide outside the off stump with the angle, left alone
presses forward and pushes the length delivery to cover point
too full, Misbah drives it going down on a knee and Nathan stops it at cover point
short ball on middle and leg, pulled to fine leg for one
well outside off and angling away, left alone easily
back of length on middle stump, defends on the leg side
outside off on length, he lets it go
angling in towards the stumps, he stays back to defend it to leg
fuller towards off, pushed down to mid on for a quick single
back of length on the stumps, tucked to the leg side
on off stump and Akmal guides it to backward point
short of length towards the off stump with the angle and Akmal gets off the mark by whipping it to the leg side for a powerful four
tries another one - this one outside off with an extravagant drive but misses
back of length outside off, punched off the back foot to backward point
closer to the off stump from short of length, defends it close to himself
swings it away this time from outside off, left alone
short of length outside off, cut off the back foot to point
short ball on the leg side, he shuffles across and pulls to fine leg for one
bouncer on the off side with the angle, he lets it go
gets room and Misbah swings his arms by driving it wide of cover right in the gap for a powerful four
bouncer down the leg side for a wide
coming in from outside off, he defends it back to the bowler
drives on the off side but gets an inner edge down to mid on for a quick single
shorter and wider outside off, cut off the back foot to sweeper cover
bit too full and he lofts it straight down the ground for four, mid on is in and he makes use of it
short ball outside off, guides it to third man off the glove
length delivery outside off, defends it close to himself on the off side
guides the short of length ball late to third man for one
short outside off, pulled down to mid on off the back foot
angles in a bouncer, Misbah looks to hook but lets it go in the end
143kmh, presses forward and blocks it into the covers
bit too full on the stumps, driven down to mid on
fullish around off, flicked to the leg side
slightly full on off and it's flicked to midwicket again
shaping it away outside off, he helps it to point
full outside off again, not much room, pushed to the off side
slightly short outside off, pulled down to long on for one
short of length outside off, stands back and pushes it to long on
draws a thick outside edge outside off for one to third man
guides it late to third man from outside off
fullish on the off stump, he pushes it back on the off side
heaves on the leg side but gets an inside edge past the stumps on the leg side for a four behind square
full this time outside off, driven to sweeper cover for one
bangs in the bouncer, Misbah sways out of the line and it's given a wide
short of length outside off and he defends off the back foot. That's drinks again
full outside off, he drives it down to mid off where an excellent fielding effort sends Misbah back
slower one outside off, turned down to long on for one
lbw appeal from Elliott and Ronchi as Misbah is struck on the pad, but outside leg and was going down further
he's yorked him with a slower ball! Elliott sent a wobbly seam down the pitch, Umar moved across a bit and the ball sneaked under his bat to rattle the stumps. Umar looks back in disbelief
angles it in towards the batsman, tucked to square leg for one
another slower and full delivery on the stumps, pushed down carefully to long on
back of length outside off, cuts it to deep backward point for one
fullish outside the off stump, pushed down to mid off
pushes the length delivery from outside off to cover point
bangs in the bouncer towards the batsman, he ducks under it
short of length outside off, steers it to point
cuts it in from outside off, he defends it back
slower one strays down the leg side and goes off the edge down leg
outside off on length, he defends it to cover point
thick edge and that runs away to the third man boundary fine on the off side for four. It was touch short of length and had some room, Misbah threw his at and got an edge to get his fifty
angling in this time, flicked to square leg
fullish on the stumps, pushed down to long on for one
cuts it in slightly, pushed down to mid on
floats one up just on off stump, pushed to the short midwicket
tossed up slightly wider, Sarfraz opens the face and runs it fine of short third man for a single
lots of air again, yorker length. Misbah moves across and tries to whip to leg but finds short mdiwicket
another flighted one worked to leg. Misbah wanted a single but they decide against
shorter and flatter, again turned to short midwicket
a tight over brings a reverse sweep from Misbah, who misses the ball. Big appeal but it's turned down
poor start for the bowler. That's short and wide but Sarfraz doesn't throw much at it. Manages to get it in between cover and point for two
length ball angled into the stumps. Sarfraz chaps this to leg and wants a run, but is turned back by Misbah as Anderson fields

Sarfraz what have you done? He backs himself to clear deep square leg with a sweep picked up from outside off stump, but he doesn't hit it well enough to get it over the man there, who gobbles it comfortably.
no messing about there. Anderson overpitches outside off, and Afridi reaches out to slam it high over the covers for a boundary
full again, but slightly wider. Afridi keeps it on the carpet this time and slices it in front of point for a couple
length ball on off stump, Afridi brings out a defensive shot to end the over
length outside off, Misbah turns the face and runs it to third man
Afridi has clearly taken issue with the run rate, and now slams a length ball high over wide mid on, for a one bounce four.
good response by Milne, who aims a short one at the body. Afridi has a swing of course, trying to swat it over mid on again, but misses
that's a lovely shot. Another short one on off stump, Afridi backs away slightly and pokes that just wide of slip, and there's more than enough pace on the ball to beat third man
shorter and closer to the body, and Afridi is beaten for pace here I think, as he tries to deflect that one fine of third man as well
length outside off stump. Afridi drives at it but misses the ball
full outside off. Misbah drives this square, straight to point
length ball wide of off stump. Misbah turns the strike over by pushing this through a gap in the covers

dropped by Brendon McCullum. Don't often see that. Afridi sees a shortish ball outside off stump and tries to flat-bat that over mid on, but only gets a top edge. McCullum runs back from mid on and comfortably gets his hands to it, but the ball spills out and the batsmen run two
boom! Slower ball, back of a length. Afridi clears the front leg and swings this high over deep square leg for a six. Is this revenge for Anderson breaking his world record?
full ball on off stump, slogged over mid on, but a fielder in the deep keeps it to two
full and on off stump, driven straight to mid on
angled in from just outside off, tucked to the leg side for one
short ball, Afridi pulls it behind square through the aerial route and gets a top edge to the backward square leg boundary for four
too full now and he drives it firmly, but straight to cover
short ball outside off this time, Afridi throws his bat at it and gets another edge over the infield for four. Behind square on the off side now
attempts a yorker and Afridi flicks it to deep midwicket for one
presses forward and defends the ball back to the bowler
he's on fire! Lofts this length delivery straight down the ground over the long off boundary for four, one-bounce and over the rope
another edge, another four! This was full outside off, he heaved hard and the thick outside edge just beat short third man for four
full and wide, hammers it with a drive to sweeper cover for one
that's way outside the off stump, wide for the adjacent pitch as well
takes a step across and tucks it to midwicket this time
swing and a miss! Short of length and well outside off, he flashes and misses
angled into the pads and it's deflected to square leg for a leg bye
goes back in the crease and punches it down to long on for one
mid off is in so he dances down the pitch to take it on the full and lofts it straight over the bowler for six
the angle doesn't make a difference, he makes room and lofts it over the cover boundary by going down on a knee for six more. That's his fifty of just 21 balls
cuts it towards short third man for one
waits for it to turn and guides to short third man and he sends Afridi back
helps it with the turn to deep midwicket for one
starts with a slower wide down the leg side
back of length outside off, punched to cover point for a quick single and Misbah tumbles at the bowler's end while completing the run
clever shot - paddles the ball from outside off fine down the leg side even though he took his eyes off the bat
slightly fuller and he paddles it again. This one to fine leg for two runs
makes room to hammer the full ball, does middle as it rolls down to long on for one

Misbah also tries a lofted shot but he holes out to deep midwicket. It was a fullish delivery on the pads and he whipped the flick from the middle of the bat but it wasn't enough to clear Latham in the deep
slightly full outside off, pushed back to the bowler
you bowl him a short ball, he'll put it away! It was outside leg, he pulled and found the gap between fine leg and deep midwicket for four
full outside off, driven into the covers
pulls, that goes high towards midwicket, but lands safe! It was a top edge off a short ball after he was unable to swing his arms properly and it fell wide of square leg
he gives the batsman room and he gives a catch to backward point! It was a short ball outside off from Boult, Bhatti swing his bat, seeing the width, and handed it straight to Guptill
full and outside off with the angle, left alone
short of length on middle and leg, defended on the leg side
he gets Afridi in his last over! Pitched it up on the stumps, Afridi lofted it straight down the ground and Guptill takes another catch, coming in from long on
slightly full on off, pushed back by Irfan
moves away a bit and leaves the away-swinging delivery outside off
140kmh, beats him with a full delivery outside off as Irfan drives and misses
full on off now, Irfan pushes at it and gets a thick outside edge to third man for one
presses forward and he also gets off the mark by edging to third man
length delivery angled across, pushed off the back foot to the off side
pitched up around off, driven back past the bowler to mid off for one
back of length outside the off stump, left alone
swings and misses at the full delivery outside off. It was a half-volley but he missed
loud appeal for caught behind, turned down! NZ review and replays show there was no edge as the full ball went past the outside edge
fuller outside off, pushed into the covers
mid off is in and he comes down the track to loft it down the ground from outside off for four
back of length outside off, he defends on the off side
that's it, Pakistan finish off on 210. Ehsan got a full delivery and in an attempt to go over the infield again he hands a catch to Baz at mid on

inn2.comm: loud appeal first ball for lbw, umpire says no. It might have hit him in front of the stumps but looked slightly high and replays show it pitched outside the leg stump. Good thing Pakistan didn't review
full and outside leg, flicked away nicely off the pads in the air for four! Can't bowl there to Baz
back of length outside the off stump, he defends off the back foot
bit of inswing outside leg, he tries to flick again and takes it on the pad

beats him with a back of length delivery that shaped in a bit, got Baz on the pad as he went on his toes to play it on leg, but the ball sneaked through the gap between bat and pad. Irfan appealed, but turned down
back of length delivery down leg, tucked to fine leg for one
inside edge onto the pad as he tries to push the fullish ball down the track
outside the off stump now, driven into the covers off the front foot
there you go, he charges down the track towards leg stump and slashes the back of length delivery over the covers for four
140kmh, sees some room with the full delivery outside off, drives firmly but gets another edge onto his pad
that's too short outside off and Baz cuts it square of the wicket nicely between backward point and cover point for another cracking four
he wants more - comes down the track again, doesn't middle it this time but gets enough bat on that to send the fullish delivery to the midwicket boundary with a slog
right on middle stump, Guptill drives it on the leg side and gets a thickish inside edge to get four at the midwicket boundary. Had he missed, he was gone
angles this one away from the batsman from outside off, Guptill leaves
crashed through the covers! Too full outside off, he got on the front foot a little bit and crunched it with a cover drive
back of length outside the off stump, left alone again
full toss and the result is the same! He got room too and swung his arms nicely for another powerful drive through the covers, nobody moved
back of length delivery past the batsman down leg for a wide
back of length and angled across, Guptill leans forward and leaves

he as going for too many shots and gets this one from the toe of the bat to be taken at point. Made room for the ball outside off, swung his bat hard and got an edge that went high in the air for Shehzad at point
back of length delivery outside off, pushed to backward point
pulls the short ball and sends it wide of deep square leg for two
back of length outside off, he defends it to cover off the back foot
140kmh, goes back in the crease to defend it down to mid off
back of length and angling in, defends on the leg side now
touch back of length outside off, left alone with a forward lean
angling in from outside off, defends it to cover now
short ball and swings it towards the leg side
stays on the back foot and defends the ball from off stump to mid on
back of length outside off, left alone

nasty short ball from Irfan, falls just short of backward square leg! The ball forced Latham on the back foot, he hopped on his toes and put his bat in front of the face, nearly gloved it to the fielder
back of length outside off, punched down to mid off
short ball angled down the leg side for a wide
flashes and misses! It was a short ball with room outside off, Guptill went on his toes to cut it over the infield but didn't connect
back of length and swinging in now, defends it down to mid on
puts his front foot forward and defends the length ball to cover
goes back in the crease now and punches it on the off side
leans forward and pushes to cover point
leaves the back of length delivery outside off
gets off the mark with a risky single - pushes the fullish delivery to mid on and takes off, Afridi stops it to his left and turns around to throw but doesn't hit the stumps as Latham slides in
short ball, he pivots on the back foot and pulls it well to find the gap between short fine leg and deep midwicket for four
back of length from leg and Guptill swats it in the air just wide of midwicket for another four. He gets on top of the short balls pretty well
angles it across the batsman from outside off, left alone
bouncer to end the over, Guptill hooks and misses this time
back of length on leg, Latham defends and gets an edge to point
short outside leg, Latham tucks it fine down the leg side off the hips for four. Cheeky shot
that's a beauty! Gets room outside off and punches it square of the wicket, past backward point for a lovely four
back of length outside off, defended to cover
nice shape as he swings it in from outside off, Latham lets it go
back of length outside off, doesn't bounce as much as he pushes to cover
132kmh, pretty straight on middle and off, Guptill gets a thick outside edge to point
slightly back of length around off, Guptill punches it back
length delivery on middle and leg, defends it back to the bowler
room outside off, Guptill cuts and Shehzad dives full length to his right to stop it with one hand. Superb effort
outside off on length and he slogs it in the big gap on the leg side to the midwicket boundary for four. Didn't middle it, but got enough to put it in the gap
leans forward and defends it to cover point now
back of length outside off, cuts it uppishly to third man
back of length delivery, tucked to midwicket for one
angles in a short ball and Latham defends it back
length delivery outside off, pushed down the ground to mid off
gets room and cuts it away to the right of backward point for four. That raced away to the boundary
fuller around off, driven straight to extra cover
touch back of length outside off, punched to backward point
that's a lovely straight drive lofted down the ground! Adil pitched it up on the stumps and Guptill lofted it back over the bowler's head for four
fullish on middle and leg, flicked to deep square leg for one
reaches out for this one outside off and drives to backward point
cuts on the off side and chops it past the stumps with an inside edge to beat the keeper for four
too full outside off, driven nicely to sweeper cover for one
short and wide outside off, no turn, he chases and misses
not as wide now as it's flighted outside off, Latham pokes and misses
bit too short, Latham rocks back and pulls it with some power to the square-leg boundary for four over the umpire's head
quicker on off and angling away, defended back to Afridi
on leg stump now, tucked to midwicket now

Lala has struck in his first over! He hasn't been turning these, this one skid away from outside off, Latham played inside the line and pushed at it, got an outside edge for the keeper. Edges and walks, umpire also gives it out
towards the leg side, clipped off the pads to deep fine leg for one
draws a thick outside edge as Taylor pushed at it in front of off and the ball held its line to go past point
back of length on midlde, pushed down to mid on for one
on length on off, defends on the leg side
room outside off, Taylor cuts to backward point after a bounce
in the corridor outside off, drives it gently to point
drifts it in towards the stumps, pushed to midwicket off the front foot
little wide outside off, cut off the back foot to point
coming in towards middle stump, pushed to short cover
flighted and full outside off, driven to short cover
darts this in towards the stumps, Guptill defends it late dangerously on the off side
excellent running as this one from middle and leg was tucked to backward square leg and they came back quickly for the second
shortish outside off, Taylor cuts it fiercely but straight to backward point
leading edge falls short of mid off! Taylor closed the face of the bat for the middle and leg delivery, did it too early and the edge went to mid off but didn't carry
back of length outside off, that was cut so hard they took two despite Shehzad at backward point getting a hand to it
short of length on off, defends it back
short ball and Taylor gets inside the line to pull it between long on and deep midwicket for four in the gap
goes off the helmet as Taylor hooked the short ball and that went over first slip for two leg byes. Time for drinks
good length ball outside the off stump. Pushes it to the leg side
goes off the outside edge to short third man for one
slightly slow outside off, pushed off the front foot to cover point
pitched up outside off, Taylor tries to paddle it fine but misses
turns in the googly from outside off, Taylor cuts to backward point
slightly flat outside off, pushed to cover with a forward lean
draws him forward as Guptill drives it square to deep point
short of length and outside off, left alone
on good length this time outside off, left again
